{"id":844,"date":"2009-06-02T07:42:30","date_gmt":"2009-06-02T12:42:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/whipping_a_classic_miracle.php"},"modified":"2009-06-02T07:42:30","modified_gmt":"2009-06-02T12:42:30","slug":"whipping_a_classic_miracle","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/whipping_a_classic_miracle.php","title":{"rendered":"Whipping a Classic Miracle"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/miracle_whip_bottle.jpg\" alt=\"Miracle Whip Packaging, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/brands.kraftfoods.com\/MiracleWhip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Miracle Whip<\/a>, the zingy alternative to mayo, has apparently seen better days in terms of mayo-alternative ubiquity and has re-entered the market positioning itself to the 18-to-34-year-old demographic. Which typically means some sort of social application, in their case Zingr, but that&#8217;s the least interesting part of this. The new label and logo are remarkably Old School, reversing the order of Before\/Afters in consumer packaging by ditching the swirls and overly friendly and loopy typography for an almost disarming simplicity. Apparently all the thrift shopping of vintage stuff by the 18- and 34-year-olds has finally paid off and that oldish look can feel new again. Fingers crossed, this will be the first of many consumer brands to revert back from the crazy scripts and wild backgrounds.<\/p><!--more--><p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/miracle_whip_comparison.jpg\" alt=\"Miracle Whip Packaging, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span class=\"small\"><strong>Old and new bottles, side by side. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.flickr.com\/photos\/the_britters\/3570227674\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Photo by Bee Forks<\/a>.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/miracle_whip_tvad.jpg\" alt=\"Miracle Whip TV AD\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span class=\"small\"><strong>Frame from new TV commercial by <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mcgarrybowen.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">mcgarrybowen<\/a>. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.brandfreak.com\/2009\/05\/miracle-whip-will-not-just-sit-there-quietly-like-that-pathetic-mayo.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Image source<\/a>.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span class=\"small\"><strong>Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.kilobytecouture.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Brittany Forks<\/a> for the tip.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Empty\" \/>","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[9,51,26],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/844"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=844"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/844\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=844"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https